The paper discusses the expressiveness of hypergraphs for uncertainty propagation using the Shenoy/Shafer method, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions a method for recovering tree-structured belief networks, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of conditional distributions and belief functions also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
